                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.035,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 64825,
                                "text": "Mr. Chief Justice Rehnquist:The opinion of the Court in Number 96-5955, Richards against Wisconsin will be announced by Justice Stevens."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.035,
                        "stop": 98.397,
                        "byte_start": 64825,
                        "byte_stop": 422181,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.035,
                                "stop": 29.698,
                                "byte_start": 64825,
                                "byte_stop": 147477,
                                "text": "Two years ago in a case called Wilson against Arkansas, we held that the Fourth Amendment to the Federal Constitution incorporates the common law requirement that police officers entering a dwelling has knocked on the door and announced their identity and purpose before attempting forceable entry."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.698,
                                "stop": 51.777,
                                "byte_start": 147477,
                                "byte_stop": 235875,
                                "text": "At the same time, we recognized that the flexible requirement of reasonableness should not be read to mandate a rigid rule of announcement that ignores countervailing law enforcement interest and left to the lower courts the task of determining the circumstances under which an unannounced entry is reasonable under the Fourth Amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 51.777,
                                "stop": 69.753,
                                "byte_start": 235875,
                                "byte_stop": 307764,
                                "text": "In this case, the Wisconsin Supreme Court concluded that our decision in Wilson did not foreclose a categorical rule allowing police officers to forgo the knock-and-announce requirement in every felony drug investigation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 69.753,
                                "stop": 76.265,
                                "byte_start": 307764,
                                "byte_stop": 333782,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari to consider whether this was a proper application of our holding in Wilson."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 76.265,
                                "stop": 85.241,
                                "byte_start": 333782,
                                "byte_stop": 369727,
                                "text": "In the unanimous opinion filed with the clerk today, we disapproved the Wisconsin Court\u0027s blanket exception to knock-and-announce."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 85.241,
                                "stop": 98.397,
                                "byte_start": 369727,
                                "byte_stop": 422181,
                                "text": "Nevertheless, based on the particular facts of this case, we affirm that court\u0027s judgment because the no knock entry in this case was reasonable under the circumstances."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
